main event: Two separate UFO sightings reported by military personnel on Guam on September 25, 1961.
interesting points: The first sighting was a rapidly moving, cylindrical mass of orange flame that crossed the sky in about 5 seconds.
The second sighting was a cylindrical mass of orange flame, about the size of a grapefruit, that moved rapidly across the sky in 3-4 seconds.
The sightings were reported by an Air Force Captain and a SMSGT, who were deemed reliable observers.
Weather conditions were clear with scattered high clouds, and the moon was shining.
The Air Force could not determine a natural explanation for the sightings and considered the possibility of a re-entry of a space vehicle.
